               java.lang.String paymentAmount,
               java.lang.String status,
               java.lang.Long timeCreated,
               java.lang.Long timeAccepted)
        Constructor method required to instantiate an instance of the Request class.
        Parameters:
        riderId - The id of the rider in a request
        driverId - The id of the rider in a request. Can be null if the driver is not assigned yet
        startLocationName - The human-friendly name of the start location for a request
        startLongitude - The longitude of the start location, stored as a long
        startLatitude - The latitude of the start location, stored as a long
        endLocationName - The human-friendly name of the end location for a request
        endLongitude - The longitude of the end location, stored as a long
        endLatitude - The latitude of the end location, stored as a long
        paymentAmount - The amount that will be charged for this request, stored as a string
        status - The status of the current request. A string that is one of: "INCOMPLETE, "ACTIVE", "COMPLETE", OR "CANCELLED"
        timeCreated - The time a request was first created, given as a long representing seconds since epoch
        timeAccepted - The time a request was first accepted by a driver, given as a long representing seconds since epoch
